# No emojis — pixel icons only

Do not use emojis or Unicode pictographs in game UI, data, scenes, or copy (e.g. hearts, crowns, tools, faces, stars).

## Instead

- Add or reuse pixel art in `assets/icons/` (16–32px, nearest-neighbor scaling).
- Load icons through `PixelIconArt` in `scripts/ui/pixel_icon_art.gd`.
- Show icons with `TextureRect` or `Button.icon`, paired with `Label` text when needed.
- Tournament opponents use an `icon` field (opponent id), not `emoji`.

## Examples

```gdscript
# BAD
label.text = "♥ %d" % hearts
tooltip_body.text = "Win all three games 🎉"

# GOOD
hearts_count.text = str(hearts)
icon_rect.texture = PixelIconArt.get_icon("heart")
```

When adding a new icon, draw it in `PixelIconArt` (or add a matching PNG under `assets/icons/`) and keep the palette consistent with existing badges and dice art.
